\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The campaign we\'92re playing is called \'93The Battle of the Men in the Pompy Helmets\'94, and I\'92m surprised to admit it\'92s pretty fun so far, though all we\'92ve done is \'93roll-up\'94 our characters. Normand says that\'92s the \'93first, most-fun part\'94 of Role-Playing. It is pretty fun. My character is a Paladin, who is a wicked-awesome warrior nun from the Western Isles [Westfarian Isles -MM], with a magic BrightSword, called Saint Hubert. I named it that, because Normand said I could name it anything. Maeve doesn\'92t like the name very much. She thinks it\'92s a stupid name for an enchanted sword [It is. -MM], but I think it\'92s funny and Normand thought it was hilarious. He even used a swear word to say how hilarious it was, but his girlfriend Claudette Eclaire got angry about that and then he felt bad about it and gave us more potato chips. He asked us not to tell Aunt Bee he used a swear word, and I\'92m like, whatever. We hear worse words at school all the time. They [Claudette and Normand! -MM] met there last year, during the Halloween 2026 stocking season. Sexy stuff. They hate it when Maeve says that out loud, to get a reaction. [I object to that -MM]}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
