\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Maeve waited as patiently as she tended to for Liz for finish reviewing her edits, so she could upload the journal to the school\'92s Story Archive website. Liz was sitting across from her at Tim\'92s, half through her half-hot-chocolate-half-decaf, which the staff at the local coffee shop would always sneak her with amused winks, since  the girls were only fourteen and shouldn\'92t be drinking coffee, even if it\'92s only half coffee, and it\'92s decaf, and it\'92s probably not really coffee anyway. That was what Blueberry said. Blueberry never came into the coffee shop with them, she was boycotting places that sold animal products, which sadly included milk and butter and most of the good things. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The coffee shop staff knew that \'93I want a half hot chocolate\'94 meant \'93and make the other half coffee\'94. They always made that part decaf, but it still felt to the girls like they were drinking coffee, sort of, like adults. Neither girl wanted to admit it tasted a lot worse than just plain hot chocolate. Taste wasn\'92t the point. Blueberry carried a thermos of water around with her, and never seemed to want to drink anything else. Maeve thought that was a little boring, but also kind of envied how healthy Bex always looked. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Bex had decided that Summer she wasn\'92t Bex anymore, and wanted to be called Blueberry. Maeve and Liz didn\'92t mind, that was a cool name, and Bex had already had two other names before that. She tried names on like hats. She was an artist. She dreamed of going to community college to learn how to teach social activism when she finished high school (an absolute requirement in the Lee-Daniels household, artist or not). In the meantime, she practiced her activism by being mostly-vegan and boycotting Tim\'92s (naturally), and also Too-Toonies, the recently renamed dollar store at the far end of the town. The girls weren\'92t sure where Blueberry was at the moment \'96 this was a meeting between author and editor anyway, which she tended to find boring.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Liz was reading the journal edits with her usual look of polite interest and serious consideration. Maeve didn\'92t understand what was taking her so long to finish, it was a short journal entry and her edits were pretty straightforward. She had pulled her punches, in fact. Liz Bright was the brightest student in school, but her writing, in Maeve\'92s opinion, needed work. Maeve had offered to help her by editing her journal entries for clarity, and then submitting them to the school\'92s Story Archives, where stories and journals that are not full of secrets could be kept by the students, like a kind of time capsule, and then opened again when they turned a certain age. Each kid was allowed to set how much time their capsule would remain closed \'96 anything from a day to 50 years. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Maeve wrote in hers all the time, mostly theories and observations. She had been a bit upset when the Story Archive site was first launched, because the maximum time allowed on the Stories had initially been 9 years. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Maeve wanted to set hers to one thousand years, but Mr. MacReady said that was not possible, because the number selector field only had space for 1 digit. Maeve had taken coding since grade primary and new this was a stupid reason, but liked her history teacher too much to make that big a deal about it, so she went to Principal Gantt instead and offered to change the number selector to support 3 digits (she was willing to go with 999 years instead of 1000), which made Gantt call a meeting with Mr. MacReady and all three of them spent the rest of the afternoon in the Inner Sanctum, looking at the site\'92s source code until Maeve pointed to where the selector\'92s digit count was set, and the change was made, to the delight of the principal (who had never seen \'93code\'94 before), and the concern of the history teacher, who knew where his students would likely take this.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Word quickly got around after that, and a lot of the kids started experimenting with wildly different \'93time encapsulations\'94 on their journal entries \'96 the notes that were reminder messages would be set to a few days, messages to themselves as older teenagers (things like, \'93don\'92t do drugs!\'94, and \'93don\'92t have babies too young!\'94, and \'93don\'92t get a credit card!\'94 were common helpful notes to older selves), and messages to their children, grandchildren, or great, great, great grandchildren had even longer time frames. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
This posed a problem for the school. The website project had been funded by parents interested in supporting their children\'92s writing education, and also as a way to monitor things if a child got into trouble, or began acting strangely. Messages with short time spans tended to have information about things going on in the kids\'92 lives, immediate plans, cries for help in some cases. Pattern-matching algorithms from the local university\'92s Comp Sci department would look for triggering phrases, words, and structures, and alert the parents when these things were flagged, without breaching the privacy of the kids\'92 journals. }
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
In the event of real problems, parents, guardians, and / or police could secure permission to read the journals, as in the case of eleven-year-old Bently Johanssen, who disappeared for a day-and-a-half the previous Winter, and was found trying to hitchhike to Arkansas, after his parents got access to his journal and discovered he had tried to look up his birth parents on Facebook and ended up friending somebody claiming to be his mother. Bently had only made it about 10 kilometers down the road, and had been camping behind a roadsign waiting for trucks heading for America. He was a boy scout and had all the gear. It was a pretty sweet camp.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl256\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa160\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\hich\af0\langfe4105\dbch\af3\afs22\lang1025\cf0\loch\f3\fs22\lang4105\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Messages written for audiences hundreds of years in the future were a whole different sort of thing. }
